+	   leave Mac OS X with at least 8 GB.  If you prefer not to use the
+	   VMWare GUI, make sure to set `memsize = "8192"` in the CoaL
+	   `USB-headnode.vmx` file.  If this is not done, the CoaL VM will page
+	   rapidly once it hits VMware's default memory limit (4G--which is too
+	   small for this system), and operations will contend for resources.  
+	   As the VM attempts to perform massive amounts of disk I/O to keep up
+	   with the system's demands, it will slow down and eventually fail to 
+	   meet them.
 
 1. When you are prompted with the GRUB menu press the down arrow.
 
